  "text": "The cDNA of extracellular portion of various NKLRs was fused in frame to the cDNA of the Fc portion of human Ig. The NKLRIg fusion proteins were produced in COS-7 cells and purified on a protein G column as previously described [CITATION_1] . Proteins were routinely tested in SDS PAGE for degradation. NKLR-Ig fusion proteins were kindly provided by Dr Ofer Mandelboim.",
